  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <l>TEares in your eyes, and passions in your harts,</l>
   <l>VVith mournfull grace vouchsafe <hi>Matildas</hi> story:</l>
   <l>The subiect sad, a King to act the parts</l>
   <l>Of his owne shame, to others endlesse glory.</l>
   <l>But such is sinne, where lawlesse lust is raigning,</l>
   <l>Sweet to the taste, till all turnes to infection,</l>
   <l>VVhen count is cast, a reckoning is remaining,</l>
   <l>VVhich must be payd, but not at our election.</l>
   <l>Perrill and Greefe, the interest of Pleasure,</l>
   <l>Spending the stock that Danger long was gayning,</l>
   <l>Makes soule and body banckrupt of that treasure,</l>
   <l>VVhich vainly spent, what helps our fond complayning?</l>
   <l>O that my lines could so the Author grace,</l>
   <l>As well his vertues merit prayse and place.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>R. L. Esquire.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
